ent approach to evaluation. This is essential reading for under-graduate and post-graduate students of policy analysis and public sector management, and those who are involved in the planning and evaluation of public policies and services.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mai 2023) 0aPolitical planningxDecision making. 0aPublic administrationxDecision making. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / General.2bisacsh1 aPhillips, Ceri, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aThomas, Paul, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2013-1995z97831111962130 cprintz978184742914840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781847429162423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781847429162/original  a978-3-11-119621-3  Bristol University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2013-1995c1995d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles